Company Overview of Bessemer Investment Management LLC



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Bessemer Investment Management LLC is a privately owned investment manager. It provides its services to banking and thrift institutions and investment companies. The firm manages separate client-focused equity, fixed income, and balanced portfolios for its clients. It also manages mutual funds and hedge funds for its clients. Additionally, the firm also manages fund of funds for its client. It invests in the public equity and fixed income markets across the globe. The firm also invests in the alternative investments markets, in hedge funds, real estate, and private equity; through ann external manager. For its equity investments, the firm primarily invests in value and growth stocks of all-c...
Bessemer Investment Management LLC is a privately owned investment manager. It provides its services to banking and thrift institutions and investment companies. The firm manages separate client-focused equity, fixed income, and balanced portfolios for its clients. It also manages mutual funds and hedge funds for its clients. Additionally, the firm also manages fund of funds for its client. It invests in the public equity and fixed income markets across the globe. The firm also invests in the alternative investments markets, in hedge funds, real estate, and private equity; through ann external manager. For its equity investments, the firm primarily invests in value and growth stocks of all-cap companies, including large-cap, mid-cap, and small-cap companies. For its fixed income investments, it typically invests cash and short-term securities, taxable bonds, municipal bonds, and investment-grade securities. The firm employs a combination of fundamental, quantitative, and qualitative analysis with a bottom-up investment approach. It employs a mix of in-house and external research to make its investment decisions. The firm operates as a subsidiary of Bessemer Trust Company, N.A. Bessemer Investment Management was founded in 1907 and is based in New York, New York with additional offices in Atlanta, Georgia; Boston, Massachusetts; Chicago, Illinois; Dallas, Texas; Grand Cayman, Cayman Islands; London, United Kingdom; Los Angeles, California; Miami, Florida; Naples, Florida; Palm Beach, Florida; San Francisco, California; Washington, District Of Columbia; Wilmington, Delaware; and Woodbridge, New Jersey.
Detailed Description


